# Daily Driver Workspace

This directory is a [daily-driver](https://github.com/skoonin/daily-driver) workspace.
It holds your personal context, task tracker, job search data, and Claude session scaffolding.

## Day-to-day commands

```
daily-driver day-start        # open a Claude session to plan your day
daily-driver check-in         # mid-day check-in with Claude
daily-driver day-end          # close-out session and capture learnings
```

## Task tracker

```
daily-driver tracker add      # add a task (job, errand, milestone, etc.)
daily-driver tracker list     # list tracked tasks
daily-driver tracker update   # update status or notes on a task
daily-driver tracker stats    # summary counts by status/category
```

## Job search

```
daily-driver jobs run         # run configured job board scrapers
daily-driver jobs status      # show last-run metadata per source
daily-driver jobs prune       # archive stale rows from jobs.csv
```

## Status and focus

```
daily-driver status           # dashboard table (Rich or --json)
daily-driver focus on         # suppress check-ins while deep-focused
daily-driver focus off        # re-enable check-ins
```

## Maintenance

```
daily-driver doctor           # verify workspace integrity
daily-driver doctor --fix     # repair drift, preserve your edits
daily-driver doctor --reset   # repair drift, overwrite managed files
```

## Configuration

Edit `.dd-config.yaml` in this directory to configure categories, job sources,
daily schedule, and other workspace settings.

## Managed files

Files under `.claude/commands/daily-driver/` and `.claude/agents/daily-driver/`
are package-managed. They are updated automatically on version upgrades.
`doctor --fix` preserves your edits; `doctor --reset` overwrites them with
fresh copies from the installed package.

This `README.md` is also package-managed and follows the same lifecycle.
